{"contents":"#ifndef DRAG_MODELS_H
#define DRAG_MODELS_H

#include <stdbool.h>

/**
 * @file drag_models.h
 * @brief Standard ballistic drag model implementations
 *
 * Implements various standard drag models used in external ballistics:
 * - G1: Standard projectile (flat base, 2 caliber ogive nose)
 * - G7: Long-range boat-tail projectile (VLD bullets)
 * - G2: Aberdeen J projectile
 * - G5: Short 7.5┬░ boat-tail, 6.19 caliber tangent ogive
 * - G6: Flat base, 6 caliber secant ogive
 * - G8: Flat base, 10 caliber secant ogive
 * - GL: Lead sphere (round ball)
 */

/**
 * Enumeration of supported drag models
 */
typedef enum {
    DRAG_MODEL_G1 = 0,  /**< Standard projectile (most common) */
    DRAG_MODEL_G2,      /**< Aberdeen J projectile */
    DRAG_MODEL_G5,      /**< Short boat-tail */
    DRAG_MODEL_G6,      /**< Flat base, secant ogive */
    DRAG_MODEL_G7,      /**< Long-range boat-tail (VLD) */
    DRAG_MODEL_G8,      /**< Flat base, 10 caliber secant ogive */
    DRAG_MODEL_GL,      /**< Lead sphere (round ball) */
    DRAG_MODEL_COUNT    /**< Number of supported models */
} DragModel;

/**
 * Initialize the drag models module
 * @return 0 on success, non-zero on failure
 */
int drag_models_init(void);

/**
 * Cleanup the drag models module
 */
void drag_models_cleanup(void);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G1 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number (velocity / speed of sound)
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g1(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G7 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g7(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G2 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g2(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G5 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g5(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G6 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g6(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for G8 model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_g8(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for GL (sphere) model at given Mach number
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_gl(double mach);

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient for any supported model at given Mach number
 * @param model The drag model to use
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd), or -1.0 on error
 */
double drag_coefficient(DragModel model, double mach);

/* Forward declaration for custom drag table */
struct DragTable;

/**
 * Get the drag coefficient from a custom drag table
 * @param table Pointer to custom drag table (NULL falls back to G1)
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @return Drag coefficient (Cd)
 */
double drag_coefficient_custom(const struct DragTable* table, double mach);

/**
 * Calculate the drag retardation (deceleration) of a projectile
 *
 * @param model The drag model to use
 * @param velocity Current velocity in fps
 * @param bc Ballistic coefficient (form factor)
 * @param air_density Current air density in lb/ft┬│
 * @param speed_of_sound Speed of sound in fps
 * @return Retardation (deceleration) in ft/s┬▓
 */
double drag_retardation(DragModel model, double velocity, double bc,
                        double air_density, double speed_of_sound);

/**
 * Calculate velocity after traveling a given distance
 * Uses numerical integration with the specified drag model
 *
 * @param model The drag model to use
 * @param initial_velocity Starting velocity in fps
 * @param bc Ballistic coefficient
 * @param distance Distance traveled in feet
 * @param air_density Air density in lb/ft┬│
 * @param speed_of_sound Speed of sound in fps
 * @return Final velocity in fps
 */
double drag_velocity_at_distance(DragModel model, double initial_velocity,
                                  double bc, double distance,
                                  double air_density, double speed_of_sound);

/**
 * Calculate time of flight over a given distance
 * Uses numerical integration with the specified drag model
 *
 * @param model The drag model to use
 * @param initial_velocity Starting velocity in fps
 * @param bc Ballistic coefficient
 * @param distance Distance traveled in feet
 * @param air_density Air density in lb/ft┬│
 * @param speed_of_sound Speed of sound in fps
 * @return Time of flight in seconds
 */
double drag_time_of_flight(DragModel model, double initial_velocity,
                           double bc, double distance,
                           double air_density, double speed_of_sound);

/**
 * Get the name of a drag model
 * @param model The drag model
 * @return String name of the model (e.g., "G1", "G7")
 */
const char* drag_model_name(DragModel model);

/**
 * Parse a drag model from a string name
 * @param name String name (e.g., "G1", "G7", case insensitive)
 * @param model Output parameter for the parsed model
 * @return true if parsing succeeded, false otherwise
 */
bool drag_model_parse(const char* name, DragModel* model);

// ============================================================================
// Standard Atmosphere Constants for Drag Calculations
// ============================================================================

/** Standard air density at sea level (lb/ft┬│) */
#define DRAG_STD_AIR_DENSITY    0.0765

/** Standard speed of sound at sea level (fps) */
#define DRAG_STD_SPEED_OF_SOUND 1116.45

/** Standard pressure at sea level (inHg) */
#define DRAG_STD_PRESSURE       29.92

/** Standard temperature at sea level (┬░F) */
#define DRAG_STD_TEMPERATURE    59.0

#endif // DRAG_MODELS_H

codeBlocks.content:
<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Verify include dependencies for BallisticsCalculator-iOS C modules.

.DESCRIPTION
    Parses all C source files in core/c/ and verifies:
    1. All #include "local.h" files exist
    2. All local headers are available in the project
    3. Reports any missing dependencies

.EXAMPLE
    .\verify-includes.ps1
    .\verify-includes.ps1 -Verbose
#>

[CmdletBinding()]
param(
    [string]$CorePath = "core/c"
)

$ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"

# Find project root (where core/c exists)
$scriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path
$projectRoot = Split-Path -Parent $scriptDir

if (-not (Test-Path "$projectRoot/$CorePath")) {
    # Try current directory
    if (Test-Path "./$CorePath") {
        $projectRoot = "."
    } else {
        Write-Error "Cannot find core/c directory. Run from project root."
        exit 1
    }
}

$coreDir = Join-Path $projectRoot $CorePath
Write-Host "Scanning: $coreDir" -ForegroundColor Cyan

# Get all C and H files
$cFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $coreDir -Filter "*.c"
$hFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $coreDir -Filter "*.h"

$availableHeaders = $hFiles | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }

Write-Host "`nAvailable headers:" -ForegroundColor Green
$availableHeaders | ForEach-Object { Write-Host "  $_" }

$errors = @()
$warnings = @()

foreach ($file in $cFiles) {
    Write-Verbose "Checking: $($file.Name)"
    
    $content = Get-Content $file.FullName -Raw
    $includes = [regex]::Matches($content, '#include\s+"([^"]+)"')
    
    foreach ($match in $includes) {
        $includedFile = $match.Groups[1].Value
        
        # Check if it's a local header (not system)
        if ($includedFile -notmatch "^(std|sys|sqlite3|math|ctype|stdio|stdlib|string)") {
            if ($includedFile -notin $availableHeaders) {
                $errors += [PSCustomObject]@{
                    Source = $file.Name
                    Missing = $includedFile
                }
            }
        }
    }
}

Write-Host "`n=== Include Verification Results ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan

if ($errors.Count -eq 0) {
    Write-Host "All local includes resolved successfully." -ForegroundColor Green
    Write-Host "Total C files checked: $($cFiles.Count)" -ForegroundColor Gray
    Write-Host "Total headers available: $($hFiles.Count)" -ForegroundColor Gray
    exit 0
} else {
    Write-Host "ERRORS: $($errors.Count) missing includes found:" -ForegroundColor Red
    $errors | ForEach-Object {
        Write-Host "  $($_.Source) -> $($_.Missing)" -ForegroundColor Red
    }
    exit 1
}

# State Machine Diagrams for Verification

This document contains formal state machine specifications for key subsystems.
These can be used for programmatic verification of state transitions.

## 1. DragTable Lifecycle State Machine

### States

| State | Description | Invariants |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Uninitialized | Memory not initialized | table == NULL or garbage |
| Initialized | Empty table created | count == 0, name set |
| PointsAdded | At least one point added | 1 <= count < DRAG_TABLE_MAX_POINTS |
| Sorted | Points sorted by Mach ascending | mach[i] < mach[i+1] for all i |
| Valid | Ready for interpolation | count >= 2, sorted |
| Persisted | Saved to SQLite | id > 0 |

### Transitions

| From | To | Trigger | Guard | Action |
|------|-----|---------|-------|--------|
| Uninitialized | Initialized | drag_table_init() | table != NULL | memset(0), set name |
| Initialized | PointsAdded | drag_table_add_point() | mach >= 0, cd > 0 | insert + sort |
| PointsAdded | PointsAdded | drag_table_add_point() | count < MAX | insert + sort |
| PointsAdded | Sorted | drag_table_sort() | count >= 1 | insertion sort |
| Sorted | Valid | (auto) | count >= 2 | - |
| Valid | Valid | drag_table_interpolate() | - | return Cd |
| Valid | Persisted | drag_table_save() | db != NULL | INSERT or UPDATE |
| Persisted | Valid | drag_table_load() | id > 0 | load from DB |
| Valid | Uninitialized | drag_table_delete() | id > 0 | DELETE row |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: drag_table_init(name)
    
    Initialized --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point(mach, cd)
    
    PointsAdded --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point(mach, cd)\n[count < MAX_POINTS]
    
    PointsAdded --> Sorted: drag_table_sort()
    
    Sorted --> Valid: [count >= 2]
    
    Valid --> Valid: drag_table_interpolate(mach)\nreturns Cd
    
    Valid --> Persisted: drag_table_save(db)\n[id = 0 INSERT, else UPDATE]
    
    Persisted --> Valid: drag_table_load(db, id)
    
    Valid --> [*]: drag_table_delete(db, id)
    
    note right of Valid
        Invariant: count >= 2
        Invariant: mach[i] < mach[i+1]
    end note
```

---

## 2. Ballistics Calculation Pipeline State Machine

### States

| State | Description | Invariants |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Idle | Waiting for input | - |
| InputValidation | Validating BallisticsInput | input != NULL |
| AtmosphereCalc | Computing atmospheric conditions | - |
| DragModelSelect | Selecting drag model | - |
| StandardDrag | Using G1/G7/etc. | custom_drag_table == NULL |
| CustomDrag | Using custom drag table | custom_drag_table != NULL |
| TableValidation | Validating custom table | - |
| FallbackG1 | Falling back to G1 | table invalid |
| TrajectoryIntegration | Numerical integration | - |
| OutputGeneration | Building BallisticsOutput | - |
| Complete | Result ready | output valid |
| Error | Error state | error message set |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    
    Idle --> InputValidation: ballistics_solve(input, output)
    
    InputValidation --> Error: [input == NULL]
    InputValidation --> AtmosphereCalc: [input valid]
    
    AtmosphereCalc --> DragModelSelect: atmosphere_speed_of_sound()
    
    DragModelSelect --> StandardDrag: [custom_drag_table == NULL]
    DragModelSelect --> CustomDrag: [custom_drag_table != NULL]

    CustomDrag --> TableValidation: drag_table_is_valid(table)
    
    TableValidation --> TrajectoryIntegration: [valid]
    TableValidation --> FallbackG1: [invalid]
    
    FallbackG1 --> TrajectoryIntegration: drag_coefficient_g1(mach)
    
    TrajectoryIntegration --> OutputGeneration: [range reached]
    
    OutputGeneration --> Complete: populate output struct
    
    Complete --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```

---

## 3. BC Curve Interpolation State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Uninitialized | Curve not set up |
| SinglePoint | Single BC value (no interpolation) |
| MultiPoint | Multiple BC/velocity pairs |
| Sorted | Points sorted by velocity descending |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> SinglePoint: bc_curve_init_single(bc, model)
    
    Uninitialized --> MultiPoint: bc_curve_init_array(bc[], vel[], count)
    
    SinglePoint --> SinglePoint: bc_curve_interpolate()\nreturns bc[0]
    
    MultiPoint --> Sorted: bc_curve_sort()
    
    Sorted --> Sorted: bc_curve_add_point(bc, vel)\n[count < MAX]
    
    Sorted --> Sorted: bc_curve_interpolate(vel)\nlinear interpolation
    
    note right of Sorted
        Invariant: velocity[i] > velocity[i+1]
        (descending order)
    end note
```

---

## 4. Truing Calculation State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Idle | Waiting for truing request |
| Validating | Checking input validity |
| RangeCheck | Checking minimum range |
| DropCompare | Comparing actual vs predicted |
| Bisection | Iterative BC adjustment |
| ConfidenceCalc | Computing confidence score |
| Complete | Result ready |
| Error | Invalid input or out of range |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    
    Idle --> Validating: truing_calculate_bc(input, options)
    
    Validating --> Error: [input invalid]
    Validating --> RangeCheck: [input valid]
    
    RangeCheck --> Error: [range < min_range_yards]
    RangeCheck --> DropCompare: [range sufficient]
    
    DropCompare --> Complete: [|actual - predicted| < tolerance]\nBC already correct
    DropCompare --> Bisection: [adjustment needed]
    
    Bisection --> Bisection: [!converged && iterations < max]
    Bisection --> Error: [solution outside bounds]
    Bisection --> ConfidenceCalc: [converged]
    
    ConfidenceCalc --> Complete: set adjusted_bc, factor, confidence
    
    Complete --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```

---

## 5. Database Connection State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Uninitialized | Database struct not set up |
| Initialized | Path set, not connected |
| Open | SQLite connection active |
| Migrated | Schema up to date |
| Error | Connection or query error |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: db_init(db, path)
    
    Initialized --> Open: db_open()
    Initialized --> Error: [sqlite3_open fails]
    
    Open --> Migrated: db_migrate()
    Open --> Error: [migration fails]
    
    Migrated --> Migrated: db_execute(sql)\ndb_query(sql)
    
    Migrated --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    Open --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    Error --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    note right of Migrated
        db_get_version() -> int
        db_set_version(v) -> void
    end note
```

---

## Verification Properties

### DragTable Safety Properties

1. **No interpolation on empty table**: `drag_table_interpolate(table, mach)` returns 0.0 if `count == 0`
2. **Boundary clamping**: Values outside Mach range return boundary Cd values
3. **Monotonicity preserved**: After any add_point, Mach values remain sorted ascending

### Ballistics Safety Properties

1. **Null input handled**: `ballistics_solve(NULL, output)` returns error, does not crash
2. **Custom table fallback**: Invalid custom table falls back to G1 silently
3. **Output always populated**: On success, all output fields are set

### Truing Safety Properties

1. **Range validation**: Truing fails gracefully for ranges below minimum
2. **Bounded adjustment**: BC adjustment never exceeds max_adjustment_factor
3. **Confidence bounded**: `0.0 <= confidence <= 1.0` always

---

## Formal State Encoding (for programmatic verification)

```c
typedef enum {
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_UNINITIALIZED = 0,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_INITIALIZED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_POINTS_ADDED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_SORTED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_VALID,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_PERSISTED
} DragTableState;

// Verify current state from table contents
DragTableState drag_table_get_state(const DragTable* table) {
    if (!table) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_UNINITIALIZED;
    if (table->count == 0) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_INITIALIZED;
    if (!is_sorted(table)) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_POINTS_ADDED;
    if (table->count < 2) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_SORTED;
    if (table->id == 0) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_VALID;
    return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_PERSISTED;
}
```

| Valid | Persisted | drag_table_save() | db != NULL | INSERT or UPDATE |
| Persisted | Valid | drag_table_load() | id > 0 | load from DB |
| Valid | Uninitialized | drag_table_delete() | id > 0 | DELETE row |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: drag_table_init(name)
    
    Initialized --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point(mach, cd)
    
    PointsAdded --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point(mach, cd)\n[count < MAX_POINTS]
    
    PointsAdded --> Sorted: drag_table_sort()
    
    Sorted --> Valid: [count >= 2]
    
    Valid --> Valid: drag_table_interpolate(mach)\nreturns Cd
    
    Valid --> Persisted: drag_table_save(db)\n[id = 0 INSERT, else UPDATE]
    
    Persisted --> Valid: drag_table_load(db, id)
    
    Valid --> [*]: drag_table_delete(db, id)
    
    note right of Valid
        Invariant: count >= 2
        Invariant: mach[i] < mach[i+1]
    end note
```

---

## 2. Ballistics Calculation Pipeline State Machine

### States

| State | Description | Invariants |
|-------|-------------|------------|
| Idle | Waiting for input | - |
| InputValidation | Validating BallisticsInput | input != NULL |
| AtmosphereCalc | Computing atmospheric conditions | - |
| DragModelSelect | Selecting drag model | - |
| StandardDrag | Using G1/G7/etc. | custom_drag_table == NULL |
| CustomDrag | Using custom drag table | custom_drag_table != NULL |
| TableValidation | Validating custom table | - |
| FallbackG1 | Falling back to G1 | table invalid |
| TrajectoryIntegration | Numerical integration | - |
| OutputGeneration | Building BallisticsOutput | - |
| Complete | Result ready | output valid |
| Error | Error state | error message set |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    
    Idle --> InputValidation: ballistics_solve(input, output)
    
    InputValidation --> Error: [input == NULL]
    InputValidation --> AtmosphereCalc: [input valid]
    
    AtmosphereCalc --> DragModelSelect: atmosphere_speed_of_sound()
    
    DragModelSelect --> StandardDrag: [custom_drag_table == NULL]
    DragModelSelect --> CustomDrag: [custom_drag_table != NULL]
    
    StandardDrag --> TrajectoryIntegration: drag_coefficient(model, mach)
    
    CustomDrag --> TableValidation: drag_table_is_valid(table)
    
    TableValidation --> TrajectoryIntegration: [valid]
    TableValidation --> FallbackG1: [invalid]
    
    FallbackG1 --> TrajectoryIntegration: drag_coefficient_g1(mach)
    
    TrajectoryIntegration --> OutputGeneration: [range reached]
    
    OutputGeneration --> Complete: populate output struct
    
    Complete --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```

---

## 3. BC Curve Interpolation State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Uninitialized | Curve not set up |
| SinglePoint | Single BC value (no interpolation) |
| MultiPoint | Multiple BC/velocity pairs |
| Sorted | Points sorted by velocity descending |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> SinglePoint: bc_curve_init_single(bc, model)
    
    Uninitialized --> MultiPoint: bc_curve_init_array(bc[], vel[], count)
    
    SinglePoint --> SinglePoint: bc_curve_interpolate()\nreturns bc[0]
    
    MultiPoint --> Sorted: bc_curve_sort()
    
    Sorted --> Sorted: bc_curve_add_point(bc, vel)\n[count < MAX]
    
    Sorted --> Sorted: bc_curve_interpolate(vel)\nlinear interpolation
    
    note right of Sorted
        Invariant: velocity[i] > velocity[i+1]
        (descending order)
    end note
```

---

## 4. Truing Calculation State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Idle | Waiting for truing request |
| Validating | Checking input validity |
| RangeCheck | Checking minimum range |
| DropCompare | Comparing actual vs predicted |
| Bisection | Iterative BC adjustment |
| ConfidenceCalc | Computing confidence score |
| Complete | Result ready |
| Error | Invalid input or out of range |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Idle
    
    Idle --> Validating: truing_calculate_bc(input, options)
    
    Validating --> Error: [input invalid]
    Validating --> RangeCheck: [input valid]
    
    RangeCheck --> Error: [range < min_range_yards]
    RangeCheck --> DropCompare: [range sufficient]
    
    DropCompare --> Complete: [|actual - predicted| < tolerance]\nBC already correct
    DropCompare --> Bisection: [adjustment needed]
    
    Bisection --> Bisection: [!converged && iterations < max]
    Bisection --> Error: [solution outside bounds]
    Bisection --> ConfidenceCalc: [converged]
    
    ConfidenceCalc --> Complete: set adjusted_bc, factor, confidence
    
    Complete --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```

---

## 5. Database Connection State Machine

### States

| State | Description |
|-------|-------------|
| Uninitialized | Database struct not set up |
| Initialized | Path set, not connected |
| Open | SQLite connection active |
| Migrated | Schema up to date |
| Error | Connection or query error |

### Diagram

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: db_init(db, path)
    
    Initialized --> Open: db_open()
    Initialized --> Error: [sqlite3_open fails]
    
    Open --> Migrated: db_migrate()
    Open --> Error: [migration fails]
    
    Migrated --> Migrated: db_execute(sql)\ndb_query(sql)
    
    Migrated --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    Open --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    Error --> Initialized: db_close()
    
    note right of Migrated
        db_get_version() -> int
        db_set_version(v) -> void
    end note
```

---

## Verification Properties

### DragTable Safety Properties

1. **No interpolation on empty table**: `drag_table_interpolate(table, mach)` returns 0.0 if `count == 0`
2. **Boundary clamping**: Values outside Mach range return boundary Cd values
3. **Monotonicity preserved**: After any add_point, Mach values remain sorted ascending

### Ballistics Safety Properties

1. **Null input handled**: `ballistics_solve(NULL, output)` returns error, does not crash
2. **Custom table fallback**: Invalid custom table falls back to G1 silently
3. **Output always populated**: On success, all output fields are set

### Truing Safety Properties

1. **Range validation**: Truing fails gracefully for ranges below minimum
2. **Bounded adjustment**: BC adjustment never exceeds max_adjustment_factor
3. **Confidence bounded**: `0.0 <= confidence <= 1.0` always

---

## Formal State Encoding (for programmatic verification)

```c
typedef enum {
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_UNINITIALIZED = 0,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_INITIALIZED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_POINTS_ADDED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_SORTED,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_VALID,
    DRAG_TABLE_STATE_PERSISTED
} DragTableState;

// Verify current state from table contents
DragTableState drag_table_get_state(const DragTable* table) {
    if (!table) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_UNINITIALIZED;
    if (table->count == 0) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_INITIALIZED;
    if (!is_sorted(table)) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_POINTS_ADDED;
    if (table->count < 2) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_SORTED;
    if (table->id == 0) return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_VALID;
    return DRAG_TABLE_STATE_PERSISTED;
}
```

codeBlocks.content:
<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Verify required symbols exist in compiled iOS binary.

.DESCRIPTION
    Uses nm/otool to check that all critical symbols are present
    in the compiled App binary. This verifies the linker successfully
    resolved all dependencies.

.PARAMETER BinaryPath
    Path to the compiled App binary (inside .app bundle or extracted IPA)

.EXAMPLE
    .\verify-symbols.ps1 -BinaryPath "Payload/App.app/App"
    .\verify-symbols.ps1 -BinaryPath "build/App.app/App"

.NOTES
    Requires macOS with Xcode command line tools (nm, otool).
    On Windows, this script generates the expected symbol list for
    verification on a macOS build machine.
#>

[CmdletBinding()]
param(
    [string]$BinaryPath,
    [switch]$GenerateOnly
)

# Critical symbols that MUST be present (from call_graph.json)
$criticalSymbols = @(
    # Ballistics core
    "_ballistics_init",
    "_ballistics_solve",
    "_ballistics_trajectory",
    "_ballistics_drop",
    "_ballistics_velocity",
    
    # Drag models
    "_drag_models_init",
    "_drag_coefficient",
    "_drag_coefficient_g1",
    "_drag_coefficient_g7",
    "_drag_coefficient_custom",
    
    # Drag table (PR #26 fix - these were missing before)
    "_drag_table_init",
    "_drag_table_interpolate",
    "_drag_table_is_valid",
    "_drag_table_sort",
    "_drag_table_add_point",
    
    # Atmosphere
    "_atmosphere_init",
    "_atmosphere_speed_of_sound",
    "_atmosphere_mach_number",
    
    # Database
    "_db_init",
    "_db_open",
    "_db_close",
    
    # Runtime
    "_runtime_init",
    "_runtime_cleanup",
    
    # Units
    "_units_yards_to_meters",
    "_units_fps_to_mps",
    
    # Assembly (ARM64 only)
    "_asm_coriolis_a64",
    "_asm_sincos_a64"
)

Write-Host "=== Symbol Verification ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host "Critical symbols to verify: $($criticalSymbols.Count)" -ForegroundColor Gray

if ($GenerateOnly -or -not $BinaryPath) {
    Write-Host "`nGenerating symbol checklist (no binary specified)..." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "`nTo verify on macOS, run:" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "  nm -g <binary> | grep -E '^[0-9a-f]+ T _'" -ForegroundColor White
    Write-Host ""
    Write-Host "Critical symbols that must be present:" -ForegroundColor Green
    
    foreach ($sym in $criticalSymbols) {
        Write-Host "  $sym"
    }
    
    Write-Host "`nTo check specific symbols:" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "  nm -g <binary> | grep '_drag_table_interpolate'" -ForegroundColor White
    Write-Host "  nm -g <binary> | grep '_drag_table_is_valid'" -ForegroundColor White
    
    # Output as JSON for programmatic use
    $outputJson = Join-Path (Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path) ".." "docs" "required_symbols.txt"
    $criticalSymbols | Out-File $outputJson -Encoding UTF8
    Write-Host "`nSymbol list written to: $outputJson" -ForegroundColor Gray
    
    exit 0
}

# If binary path provided, try to verify (macOS only)
if (-not (Test-Path $BinaryPath)) {
    Write-Error "Binary not found: $BinaryPath"
    exit 1
}

Write-Host "Checking binary: $BinaryPath" -ForegroundColor Cyan

# Check if we're on macOS
$isMacOS = $PSVersionTable.OS -match "Darwin" -or $env:OS -notmatch "Windows"

if (-not $isMacOS) {
    Write-Host "`nNOTE: Symbol verification requires macOS with nm/otool." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    Write-Host "Copy the symbol list above and run on your macOS build machine." -ForegroundColor Yellow
    exit 0
}

# Run nm to get symbols
try {
    $symbols = & nm -g $BinaryPath 2>&1
    $definedSymbols = $symbols | Where-Object { $_ -match '^\s*[0-9a-f]+\s+T\s+' } | 
                       ForEach-Object { ($_ -split '\s+')[-1] }
    
    Write-Host "`nDefined symbols found: $($definedSymbols.Count)" -ForegroundColor Gray
    
    $missing = @()
    $found = @()
    
    foreach ($sym in $criticalSymbols) {
        if ($sym -in $definedSymbols) {
            $found += $sym
        } else {
            $missing += $sym
        }
    }
    
    Write-Host "`n=== Results ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
    Write-Host "Found: $($found.Count)/$($criticalSymbols.Count)" -ForegroundColor $(if ($found.Count -eq $criticalSymbols.Count) { "Green" } else { "Yellow" })
    
    if ($missing.Count -gt 0) {
        Write-Host "`nMissing symbols:" -ForegroundColor Red
        foreach ($m in $missing) {
            Write-Host "  $m" -ForegroundColor Red
        }
        
        # Check for the specific PR #26 symbols
        $pr26Symbols = @("_drag_table_interpolate", "_drag_table_is_valid")
        $pr26Missing = $pr26Symbols | Where-Object { $_ -in $missing }
        
        if ($pr26Missing.Count -gt 0) {
            Write-Host "`nCRITICAL: PR #26 linker error symbols are missing!" -ForegroundColor Red
            Write-Host "The fix for drag_table.c may not have been applied correctly." -ForegroundColor Red
            exit 1
        }
        
        exit 1
    }
    
    Write-Host "`nAll critical symbols present." -ForegroundColor Green
    exit 0
    
} catch {
    Write-Error "Failed to run nm: $_"
    exit 1
}

    ```c
    #include "drag_table.h"

    double drag_coefficient_custom(const struct DragTable* table, double mach)
    {
        if (!table || !drag_table_is_valid(table)) {
            /* Fallback to G1 if no valid custom table */
            return drag_coefficient_g1(mach);
        }

    }
    ```

codeBlocks.content:
<#
.SYNOPSIS
    Verify Xcode project.pbxproj includes all required C source files.

.DESCRIPTION
    Parses project.pbxproj and verifies:
    1. All .c files in core/c/ have PBXFileReference entries
    2. All .c files have PBXBuildFile entries
    3. All .c files are in PBXSourcesBuildPhase

.EXAMPLE
    .\verify-pbxproj.ps1
    .\verify-pbxproj.ps1 -Verbose
#>

[CmdletBinding()]
param(
    [string]$CorePath = "core/c",
    [string]$PbxprojPath = "ios/App/App.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj"
)

$ErrorActionPreference = "Stop"

# Find project root
$scriptDir = Split-Path -Parent $MyInvocation.MyCommand.Path
$projectRoot = Split-Path -Parent $scriptDir

if (-not (Test-Path "$projectRoot/$CorePath")) {
    if (Test-Path "./$CorePath") {
        $projectRoot = "."
    } else {
        Write-Error "Cannot find core/c directory. Run from project root."
        exit 1
    }
}

$coreDir = Join-Path $projectRoot $CorePath
$pbxprojFile = Join-Path $projectRoot $PbxprojPath

Write-Host "Project root: $projectRoot" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host "Checking: $pbxprojFile" -ForegroundColor Cyan

if (-not (Test-Path $pbxprojFile)) {
    Write-Error "project.pbxproj not found at: $pbxprojFile"
    exit 1
}

# Get all C files that should be in the build
$cFiles = Get-ChildItem -Path $coreDir -Filter "*.c" | ForEach-Object { $_.Name }

Write-Host "`nC files in core/c/:" -ForegroundColor Green
$cFiles | ForEach-Object { Write-Host "  $_" }

# Read pbxproj content
$pbxContent = Get-Content $pbxprojFile -Raw

# Check for each file
$results = @()

foreach ($file in $cFiles) {
    $result = [PSCustomObject]@{
        File = $file
        FileReference = $false
        BuildFile = $false
        InSources = $false
    }
    
    # Check PBXFileReference (pattern: /* filename */ = {isa = PBXFileReference)
    if ($pbxContent -match [regex]::Escape("/* $file */") -and $pbxContent -match [regex]::Escape("name = $file")) {
        $result.FileReference = $true
    }
    
    # Check PBXBuildFile (pattern: /* filename in Sources */)
    if ($pbxContent -match [regex]::Escape("/* $file in Sources */")) {
        $result.BuildFile = $true
        $result.InSources = $true
    }
    
    $results += $result
}

Write-Host "`n=== Xcode Project Verification ===" -ForegroundColor Cyan
Write-Host ("{0,-25} {1,-15} {2,-12} {3,-12}" -f "File", "FileRef", "BuildFile", "InSources")
Write-Host ("-" * 65)

$missing = @()
foreach ($r in $results) {
    $status = if ($r.FileReference -and $r.BuildFile -and $r.InSources) { "OK" } else { "MISSING" }
    $color = if ($status -eq "OK") { "Green" } else { "Red" }
    
    Write-Host ("{0,-25} {1,-15} {2,-12} {3,-12}" -f $r.File, $r.FileReference, $r.BuildFile, $r.InSources) -ForegroundColor $color
    
    if ($status -eq "MISSING") {
        $missing += $r
    }
}

Write-Host ""

if ($missing.Count -eq 0) {
    Write-Host "All C files are properly included in Xcode project." -ForegroundColor Green
    exit 0
} else {
    Write-Host "WARNING: $($missing.Count) files not fully integrated:" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    foreach ($m in $missing) {
        $issues = @()
        if (-not $m.FileReference) { $issues += "no PBXFileReference" }
        if (-not $m.BuildFile) { $issues += "no PBXBuildFile" }
        if (-not $m.InSources) { $issues += "not in Sources phase" }
        Write-Host "  $($m.File): $($issues -join ', ')" -ForegroundColor Yellow
    }
    
    # Check if the critical drag_table.c is present (the PR #26 fix)
    $dragTable = $results | Where-Object { $_.File -eq "drag_table.c" }
    if ($dragTable -and $dragTable.FileReference -and $dragTable.BuildFile -and $dragTable.InSources) {
        Write-Host "`ndrag_table.c is properly included (PR #26 fix verified)." -ForegroundColor Green
        exit 0  # Not a hard failure if optional files are missing
    } else {
        Write-Host "`nCRITICAL: drag_table.c is not properly included!" -ForegroundColor Red
        Write-Host "This will cause linker errors for _drag_table_interpolate and _drag_table_is_valid" -ForegroundColor Red
        exit 1
    }
}

# Control Flow Graphs for Critical Functions

This document contains control flow graphs (CFGs) for critical functions.
Each CFG shows all execution paths for verification purposes.

---

## 1. drag_coefficient_custom (drag_models.c:421-428)

### Source Code

```c
double drag_coefficient_custom(const struct DragTable* table, double mach)
{
    if (!table || !drag_table_is_valid(table)) {
        /* Fallback to G1 if no valid custom table */
        return drag_coefficient_g1(mach);
    }
    return drag_table_interpolate(table, mach);
}
```

### CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: drag_coefficient_custom(table, mach)"]
    
    cond1{"table == NULL?"}
    cond2{"drag_table_is_valid(table)?"}
    
    path_g1["call drag_coefficient_g1(mach)"]
    path_interp["call drag_table_interpolate(table, mach)"]
    
    ret["Return Cd"]
    
    entry --> cond1
    cond1 -->|Yes| path_g1
    cond1 -->|No| cond2
    cond2 -->|No: invalid| path_g1
    cond2 -->|Yes: valid| path_interp
    path_g1 --> ret
    path_interp --> ret
```

### Path Coverage

| Path ID | Condition | Result |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| P1 | table == NULL | G1 fallback |
| P2 | table != NULL AND !is_valid | G1 fallback |
| P3 | table != NULL AND is_valid | Custom interpolation |

---

## 2. drag_table_interpolate (drag_table.c:147-186)

### CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: drag_table_interpolate(table, mach)"]
    
    check_null{"table == NULL OR count == 0?"}
    check_single{"count == 1?"}
    check_below{"mach <= min_mach?"}
    check_above{"mach >= max_mach?"}
    
    ret_zero["Return 0.0"]
    ret_first["Return cd[0]"]
    ret_last["Return cd[count-1]"]
    
    binary_search["Binary search for interval"]
    loop_cond{"high - low > 1?"}
    calc_mid["mid = (low + high) / 2"]
    check_mid{"mach[mid] <= mach?"}
    set_low["low = mid"]
    set_high["high = mid"]
    
    interpolate["t = (mach - m0) / (m1 - m0)"]
    ret_interp["Return c0 + t * (c1 - c0)"]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| ret_zero
    check_null -->|No| check_single
    check_single -->|Yes| ret_first
    check_single -->|No| check_below
    check_below -->|Yes| ret_first
    check_below -->|No| check_above
    check_above -->|Yes| ret_last
    check_above -->|No| binary_search
    binary_search --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|Yes| calc_mid
    calc_mid --> check_mid
    check_mid -->|Yes| set_low
    check_mid -->|No| set_high
    set_low --> loop_cond
    set_high --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|No| interpolate
    interpolate --> ret_interp
```

### Path Coverage

| Path ID | Condition | Result |
|---------|-----------|--------|
| P1 | table NULL or empty | 0.0 |
| P2 | Single point | cd[0] |
| P3 | mach <= min | cd[0] |
| P4 | mach >= max | cd[count-1] |
| P5 | Binary search + interpolate | Linear interpolation |

---

## 3. drag_table_is_valid (drag_table.c:188-201)

### CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: drag_table_is_valid(table)"]
    
    check_null{"table == NULL?"}
    check_count{"count < 2?"}
    loop_init["i = 1"]
    loop_cond{"i < count?"}
    check_order{"mach[i] <= mach[i-1]?"}
    loop_inc["i++"]
    
    ret_0["Return 0 (invalid)"]
    ret_1["Return 1 (valid)"]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| ret_0
    check_null -->|No| check_count
    check_count -->|Yes| ret_0
    check_count -->|No| loop_init
    loop_init --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|Yes| check_order
    check_order -->|Yes: not ascending| ret_0
    check_order -->|No: ascending| loop_inc
    loop_inc --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|No: loop done| ret_1
```

---

## 4. ballistics_solve (ballistics.c:396+)

### Simplified CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: ballistics_solve(input, output)"]
    
    check_null{"input == NULL OR output == NULL?"}
    
    init["Initialize output to zero"]
    
    get_atmosphere["Get atmosphere conditions"]
    calc_sos["speed_of_sound = atmosphere_speed_of_sound()"]
    
    check_custom{"input->custom_drag_table != NULL?"}
    
    get_drag_std["Cd = drag_coefficient(model, mach)"]
    get_drag_custom["Cd = drag_coefficient_custom(table, mach)"]
    
    integrate["Numerical integration loop"]
    
    calc_drop["Calculate drop"]
    calc_wind["Calculate wind drift"]
    calc_spin{"enable_spin_drift?"}
    calc_coriolis{"enable_coriolis?"}
    
    add_spin["Add spin drift"]
    add_coriolis["Add Coriolis effect"]
    
    populate["Populate output struct"]
    
    ret_err["Return -1 (error)"]
    ret_ok["Return 0 (success)"]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| ret_err
    check_null -->|No| init
    init --> get_atmosphere
    get_atmosphere --> calc_sos
    calc_sos --> check_custom
    check_custom -->|No| get_drag_std
    check_custom -->|Yes| get_drag_custom
    get_drag_std --> integrate
    get_drag_custom --> integrate
    integrate --> calc_drop
    calc_drop --> calc_wind
    calc_wind --> calc_spin
    calc_spin -->|Yes| add_spin
    calc_spin -->|No| calc_coriolis
    add_spin --> calc_coriolis
    calc_coriolis -->|Yes| add_coriolis
    calc_coriolis -->|No| populate
    add_coriolis --> populate
    populate --> ret_ok
```

---

## 5. truing_calculate_bc (truing.c:172-269)

### CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: truing_calculate_bc(input, options)"]
    
    init["Initialize result to zero"]
    check_options{"options == NULL?"}
    use_default["Use default options"]
    
    validate{"truing_validate_input(input)?"}
    check_range{"range >= min_range_yards?"}
    
    calc_delta["delta = actual_drop - predicted_drop"]
    check_tolerance{"abs(delta) < tolerance?"}
    
    bc_already_correct["adjusted_bc = original_bc, factor = 1.0"]
    
    set_bounds["bc_low = bc * (1 - max_adj)\nbc_high = bc * (1 + max_adj)"]
    calc_drops["drop_low = calc(bc_low)\ndrop_high = calc(bc_high)"]
    
    check_solution{"solution exists in bounds?"}
    
    bisection_loop["Bisection iteration"]
    loop_cond{"i < max_iterations AND !converged?"}
    calc_mid["bc_mid = (low + high) / 2"]
    calc_drop_mid["drop_mid = calc(bc_mid)"]
    check_converged{"abs(drop_mid - target) < tol?"}
    adjust_bounds["Adjust bc_low or bc_high"]
    loop_inc["i++"]
    
    calc_confidence["confidence = truing_confidence_score()"]
    set_result["result.adjusted_bc = bc_mid\nresult.valid = 1"]
    
    ret_err["result.valid = 0, error_message set"]
    ret_ok["Return result"]
    
    entry --> init
    init --> check_options
    check_options -->|Yes| use_default
    check_options -->|No| validate
    use_default --> validate
    validate -->|No| ret_err
    validate -->|Yes| check_range
    check_range -->|No| ret_err
    check_range -->|Yes| calc_delta
    calc_delta --> check_tolerance
    check_tolerance -->|Yes| bc_already_correct
    bc_already_correct --> ret_ok
    check_tolerance -->|No| set_bounds
    set_bounds --> calc_drops
    calc_drops --> check_solution
    check_solution -->|No| ret_err
    check_solution -->|Yes| bisection_loop
    bisection_loop --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|Yes| calc_mid
    calc_mid --> calc_drop_mid
    calc_drop_mid --> check_converged
    check_converged -->|Yes| calc_confidence
    check_converged -->|No| adjust_bounds
    adjust_bounds --> loop_inc
    loop_inc --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|No| calc_confidence
    calc_confidence --> set_result
    set_result --> ret_ok
```

---

## 6. bc_curve_interpolate (bc_curve.c:96-141)

### CFG

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry["Entry: bc_curve_interpolate(curve, velocity_fps)"]
    
    check_null{"curve == NULL OR count == 0?"}
    check_single{"count == 1?"}
    check_above{"velocity >= velocity[0]?"}
    check_below{"velocity <= velocity[count-1]?"}
    
    ret_zero["Return 0.0"]
    ret_first["Return bc[0]"]
    ret_last["Return bc[count-1]"]
    
    loop_init["i = 0"]
    loop_cond{"i < count - 1?"}
    get_bounds["v_high = velocity[i]\nv_low = velocity[i+1]"]
    check_interval{"velocity in [v_low, v_high]?"}
    
    interpolate["t = (v_high - velocity) / (v_high - v_low)\nbc = bc_high + t * (bc_low - bc_high)"]
    ret_interp["Return bc"]
    
    loop_inc["i++"]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| ret_zero
    check_null -->|No| check_single
    check_single -->|Yes| ret_first
    check_single -->|No| check_above
    check_above -->|Yes| ret_first
    check_above -->|No| check_below
    check_below -->|Yes| ret_last
    check_below -->|No| loop_init
    loop_init --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|Yes| get_bounds
    get_bounds --> check_interval
    check_interval -->|Yes| interpolate
    interpolate --> ret_interp
    check_interval -->|No| loop_inc
    loop_inc --> loop_cond
    loop_cond -->|No| ret_first
```

---

## Verification Invariants

### Pre-conditions

| Function | Pre-condition |
|----------|---------------|
| drag_coefficient_custom | None (handles NULL) |
| drag_table_interpolate | None (handles NULL) |
| drag_table_is_valid | None (handles NULL) |
| ballistics_solve | None (handles NULL) |
| truing_calculate_bc | None (handles NULL) |
| bc_curve_interpolate | None (handles NULL) |

### Post-conditions

| Function | Post-condition |
|----------|----------------|
| drag_coefficient_custom | Returns Cd >= 0.0 |
| drag_table_interpolate | Returns Cd >= 0.0 |
| drag_table_is_valid | Returns 0 or 1 |
| ballistics_solve | output fully populated OR error code |
| truing_calculate_bc | result.valid set, confidence in [0, 1] |
| bc_curve_interpolate | Returns BC >= 0.0 |

### Loop Invariants

| Function | Loop | Invariant |
|----------|------|-----------|
| drag_table_interpolate | binary search | low <= target_idx <= high |
| drag_table_is_valid | ascending check | mach[0..i-1] is strictly ascending |
| truing_calculate_bc | bisection | bc_low <= adjusted_bc <= bc_high |
| bc_curve_interpolate | interval search | velocity[0..i] > velocity_fps |

{"contents":"/*
 * Custom Drag Table Support
 *
 * Enables importing and using custom Cd vs Mach tables from:
 * - JBM Ballistics (tab-separated Mach/Cd pairs)
 * - Applied Ballistics (CSV with header)
 * - Lapua (JSON bullet profiles)
 * - Sierra (manual velocity-BC transcription)
 *
 * Based on authoritative BRL/McCoy data from Aberdeen Proving Ground.
 *
 * SPDX-License-Identifier: BSD-2-Clause
 * Signed-off-by: Ludoplex
 */

#ifndef DRAG_TABLE_H
#define DRAG_TABLE_H

#ifdef __cplusplus
extern "C" {
#endif

#include <stddef.h>

/* Forward declaration for SQLite */
struct sqlite3;
typedef struct sqlite3 sqlite3;

/* Maximum number of Mach/Cd points in a drag table */
#define DRAG_TABLE_MAX_POINTS 100

/* Maximum name length */
#define DRAG_TABLE_NAME_LEN 64

/* Source identifiers */
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_LEN 32
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_JBM    "JBM"
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_AB     "AB"
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_LAPUA  "LAPUA"
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_SIERRA "SIERRA"
#define DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_USER   "USER"

/**
 * @brief Custom drag coefficient table
 *
 * Stores Cd values as a function of Mach number.
 * Points must be sorted in ascending Mach order.
 */
typedef struct DragTable {
    double mach[DRAG_TABLE_MAX_POINTS];   /* Mach numbers (ascending) */
    double cd[DRAG_TABLE_MAX_POINTS];     /* Corresponding Cd values */
    int count;                             /* Number of valid points */
    char name[DRAG_TABLE_NAME_LEN];       /* Table name (e.g., "G1 Custom") */
    char source[DRAG_TABLE_SOURCE_LEN];   /* Source identifier */
    int id;                                /* SQLite row ID (0 if not persisted) */
} DragTable;

/* ============================================================================
 * Core Functions
 * ============================================================================ */

/**
 * @brief Initialize an empty drag table
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table structure
 * @param name Table name (NULL for empty)
 * @return 1 on success, 0 on invalid input
 */
int drag_table_init(DragTable* table, const char* name);

/**
 * @brief Add a Mach/Cd point to the table
 *
 * Points are automatically sorted by Mach number (ascending).
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table
 * @param mach Mach number
 * @param cd Drag coefficient at this Mach
 * @return 1 on success, 0 if table is full or invalid input
 */
int drag_table_add_point(DragTable* table, double mach, double cd);

/**
 * @brief Interpolate Cd at a given Mach number
 *
 * Uses binary search with linear interpolation.
 * Clamps to boundary values if Mach is outside table range.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table
 * @param mach Mach number to interpolate at
 * @return Interpolated Cd value, or 0.0 if table is invalid
 */
double drag_table_interpolate(const DragTable* table, double mach);

/**
 * @brief Check if the table is valid
 *
 * A table is valid if it has at least 2 points and
 * Mach values are in ascending order.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table
 * @return 1 if valid, 0 otherwise
 */
int drag_table_is_valid(const DragTable* table);

/**
 * @brief Sort table points by Mach number (ascending)
 *
 * Called automatically by add_point, but can be called
 * manually after bulk initialization.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table
 */
void drag_table_sort(DragTable* table);

/**
 * @brief Get the Mach range covered by this table
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table
 * @param min_mach Output: minimum Mach in table
 * @param max_mach Output: maximum Mach in table
 * @return 1 on success, 0 if table is empty
 */
int drag_table_get_range(const DragTable* table, double* min_mach, double* max_mach);

/* ============================================================================
 * Parsing Functions
 * ============================================================================ */

/**
 * @brief Parse JBM format (tab-separated Mach/Cd pairs)
 *
 * Format: "MACH\tCD\n" per line, no header.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param data Raw file data
 * @param len Length of data
 * @return Number of points parsed, or -1 on error
 */
int drag_table_parse_jbm(DragTable* table, const char* data, size_t len);

/**
 * @brief Parse CSV format (comma-separated with header)
 *
 * Format: "Mach,Cd\n" header, then "MACH,CD\n" per line.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param data Raw file data
 * @param len Length of data
 * @return Number of points parsed, or -1 on error
 */
int drag_table_parse_csv(DragTable* table, const char* data, size_t len);

/**
 * @brief Parse JSON format (Lapua-style bullet profile)
 *
 * Expects {"drag_table": [{"mach": M, "cd": C}, ...]}
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param data Raw JSON data
 * @param len Length of data
 * @return Number of points parsed, or -1 on error
 */
int drag_table_parse_json(DragTable* table, const char* data, size_t len);

/**
 * @brief Auto-detect format and parse
 *
 * Detects format based on content analysis:
 * - Starts with '{' = JSON
 * - Contains ',' and header row = CSV
 * - Tab-separated = JBM
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param data Raw file data
 * @param len Length of data
 * @return Number of points parsed, or -1 on error
 */
int drag_table_parse_auto(DragTable* table, const char* data, size_t len);

/* ============================================================================
 * File I/O
 * ============================================================================ */

/**
 * @brief Load a drag table from a file
 *
 * Auto-detects format based on content.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param path File path
 * @return Number of points loaded, or -1 on error
 */
int drag_table_load_file(DragTable* table, const char* path);

/* ============================================================================
 * SQLite Persistence
 * ============================================================================ */

/**
 * @brief Save a drag table to the database
 *
 * If table->id is 0, inserts a new row and updates table->id.
 * Otherwise, updates the existing row.
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to save
 * @param db SQLite database handle
 * @return 1 on success, 0 on error
 */
int drag_table_save(DragTable* table, sqlite3* db);

/**
 * @brief Load a drag table from the database by ID
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param db SQLite database handle
 * @param id Row ID to load
 * @return 1 on success, 0 if not found or error
 */
int drag_table_load(DragTable* table, sqlite3* db, int id);

/**
 * @brief Delete a drag table from the database
 *
 * @param db SQLite database handle
 * @param id Row ID to delete
 * @return 1 on success, 0 on error
 */
int drag_table_delete(sqlite3* db, int id);

/**
 * @brief List all drag tables in the database
 *
 * Only loads metadata (name, source, id), not full point data.
 *
 * @param db SQLite database handle
 * @param tables Array to populate
 * @param max Maximum number of tables to return
 * @param count Output: actual number returned
 * @return 1 on success, 0 on error
 */
int drag_table_list(sqlite3* db, DragTable* tables, int max, int* count);

/**
 * @brief Load a drag table from the database by name
 *
 * @param table Pointer to table to populate
 * @param db SQLite database handle
 * @param name Table name to find
 * @return 1 on success, 0 if not found or error
 */
int drag_table_load_by_name(DragTable* table, sqlite3* db, const char* name);

#ifdef __cplusplus
}
#endif

#endif /* DRAG_TABLE_H */

This is not related to the SQLite changes at all - it's a **missing source file in the Xcode project configuration**.

Let me also check other files that might be missing:

- database.c

So the missing files from the Xcode project are:
- arena.c

The critical one is `drag_table.c` which contains the `drag_table_interpolate` and `drag_table_is_valid` functions that `drag_models.c` depends on.

Now I have enough information to create a plan to fix this issue. The PR is focusing on SQLite changes but the real issue is that the Xcode project is missing `drag_table.c` (and possibly other C files).


## Module Descriptions

### 1. Units Module (`core/c/units.h`, `core/c/units.c`)

Provides comprehensive unit conversion utilities for ballistics calculations.

**Supported Conversions:**
- **Length**: yards, feet, inches, meters, centimeters, millimeters
- **Velocity**: feet per second (fps), meters per second (m/s), miles per hour (mph), kilometers per hour (km/h)
- **Mass**: grains, grams, ounces, pounds
- **Angle**: degrees, radians, MOA (minutes of angle), milliradians (mils)
- **Pressure**: inHg, hPa, mbar, psi
- **Temperature**: Fahrenheit, Celsius, Kelvin

**Key Functions:**
```c
double units_yards_to_meters(double yards);
double units_fps_to_mps(double fps);
double units_grains_to_grams(double grains);
double units_moa_to_radians(double moa);
double units_fahrenheit_to_celsius(double fahrenheit);
```

### 2. Drag Models Module (`core/c/drag_models.h`, `core/c/drag_models.c`)

Implements standard ballistic drag models for projectile trajectory calculations.

**Supported Drag Models:**
- **G1**: Standard projectile (flat base, 2 caliber ogive nose)
- **G7**: Long-range boat-tail projectile (VLD bullets)
- **G2**: Aberdeen J projectile
- **G5**: Short 7.5┬░ boat-tail, 6.19 caliber tangent ogive
- **G6**: Flat base, 6 caliber secant ogive
- **G8**: Flat base, 10 caliber secant ogive

**Key Functions:**
```c
double drag_coefficient_g1(double mach);
double drag_coefficient_g7(double mach);
double drag_retardation(DragModel model, double velocity, double bc, double air_density);
```

**Drag Coefficient Calculation:**
The drag coefficient varies with Mach number and is interpolated from standard tables:
```
Cd = f(Mach) where:
  - Subsonic (M < 0.9): Lower, relatively constant drag
  - Transonic (0.9 < M < 1.2): Rapidly increasing drag
  - Supersonic (M > 1.2): Decreasing drag with increasing Mach
```

### 3. Atmosphere Module (`core/c/atmosphere.h`, `core/c/atmosphere.c`)

Handles atmospheric calculations that affect projectile flight.

**Features:**
- Standard atmosphere model (ISA - International Standard Atmosphere)
- Altitude-based pressure and density calculations
- Temperature and humidity corrections
- Speed of sound calculations
- Air density ratio computations

**Key Functions:**
```c
double atmosphere_pressure_at_altitude(double altitude_ft);
double atmosphere_density_at_altitude(double altitude_ft);
double atmosphere_speed_of_sound(double temperature_f);
double atmosphere_density_ratio(double altitude_ft, double temperature_f, double humidity);
```

**Standard Atmosphere Model:**
```
Sea Level Conditions:
- Pressure: 29.92 inHg (1013.25 hPa)
- Temperature: 59┬░F (15┬░C)
- Density: 0.0765 lb/ft┬│ (1.225 kg/m┬│)

Lapse Rate: -3.57┬░F per 1000 ft (-6.5┬░C per 1000 m)
```

### 4. Ballistics Module (`core/c/ballistics.h`, `core/c/ballistics.c`)

The main trajectory calculation engine that integrates all other modules.

**Input Parameters:**
```c
typedef struct {
    double bullet_weight_grains;
    double muzzle_velocity_fps;
    double ballistic_coefficient;
    double sight_height_inches;
    double zero_range_yards;
    // Extended parameters (optional)
    DragModel drag_model;
    double altitude_feet;
    double temperature_fahrenheit;
    double humidity_percent;
    double wind_speed_mph;
    double wind_angle_degrees;
} BallisticsInput;
```

**Output Data:**
```c
typedef struct {
    double range_yards;
    double drop_inches;
    double drop_moa;
    double velocity_fps;
    double energy_ftlbs;
    double time_of_flight_sec;
    double wind_drift_inches;
    double wind_drift_moa;
} BallisticsOutput;
```

**Calculation Flow:**
1. Initialize atmosphere conditions
2. Calculate air density ratio
3. For each range increment:
   - Calculate velocity using drag model
   - Compute time of flight
   - Calculate drop due to gravity
   - Apply wind drift
   - Compute remaining energy

### 5. Runtime Module (`core/c/runtime.h`, `core/c/runtime.c`)

Core runtime utilities with platform-specific optimizations.

**Features:**
- String operations (strlen, strcpy, strcmp)
- Memory operations (memcpy, memset)
- Math operations with AArch64 assembly optimizations

### 6. Database Module (`core/c/database.h`, `core/c/database.c`)

SQLite wrapper for persistent storage.

**Tables:**
- `projectiles`: Bullet data (weight, BC, caliber)
- `loads`: Ammunition load data (velocity, cartridge)
- `profiles`: User shooting profiles
- `zero_data`: Zero range data for different conditions

## Data Flow

### Trajectory Calculation Flow

```
User Input (iOS UI)
```

## File Structure

```

Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ c/

Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ asm/
Γöé   ΓööΓöÇΓöÇ ops_a64.s          # AArch64 optimized operations
ΓööΓöÇΓöÇ tests/
    Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ test_ballistics.c  # Ballistics tests
    Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ test_units.c       # Unit conversion tests
    Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ test_drag_models.c # Drag model tests
    Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ test_atmosphere.c  # Atmosphere tests
    Γö£ΓöÇΓöÇ test_database.c    # Database tests
    ΓööΓöÇΓöÇ test_runtime.c     # Runtime tests
```

## Build Configuration

### Compiler Flags

```makefile
CFLAGS = -std=c11 -Wall -Wextra -O2
LDFLAGS = -lm -lsqlite3

# iOS specific
IOS_CFLAGS = -arch arm64 -isysroot $(SDKROOT)
```

### Platform Detection

```c
#ifdef __aarch64__
    // Use ARM64 optimized code paths
#else
    // Use portable C implementations
#endif
```

## Testing Strategy

### Unit Tests

Each module has corresponding unit tests:
- `test_units.c`: Conversion accuracy tests
- `test_drag_models.c`: Drag coefficient verification
- `test_atmosphere.c`: Atmosphere model validation
- `test_ballistics.c`: Integration tests

### Test Coverage

- Edge cases (zero values, negative inputs)
- Boundary conditions (subsonic/supersonic transition)
- Real-world scenarios (common cartridges)
- Cross-platform consistency

## Performance Considerations

### Optimizations

1. **Lookup Tables**: Pre-computed drag coefficient tables for fast interpolation
2. **SIMD Operations**: ARM NEON intrinsics for vector calculations
3. **Caching**: Memoization of frequently calculated values
4. **Lazy Evaluation**: Calculate only requested output fields
5. **Branchless Programming**: Arithmetic masking to avoid branch misprediction
6. **Arena Allocators**: Bump allocation with hybrid malloc() fallback

### Memory Management

- **Arena Allocators** (`core/c/arena.h/c`): Fast O(1) allocation for trajectory generation
- Static allocation where possible
- No dynamic memory allocation in hot paths (use arena instead)
- Thread-safe design for concurrent calculations
- Hybrid fallback to malloc() when arena is exhausted

### A64 Assembly Optimizations

The `core/asm/ops_a64.s` provides NEON-optimized functions for ARM64:

| Function | Description | Performance Benefit |
|----------|-------------|---------------------|
| `asm_coriolis_a64` | SIMD Coriolis with cos(az) | 2-4x faster than C |
| `asm_sincos_a64` | Parallel sin/cos computation | Reduces function call overhead |

### Branchless Techniques

Critical paths use branchless programming to avoid pipeline stalls:

```c
// Branchless interpolation (avoids if/else)
double is_valid = (double)(fabs(denom) > 1e-10);
double t = (x - x0) / (denom + (1.0 - is_valid));
return y0 + is_valid * t * (y1 - y0);

// Branchless validity masking
double t_positive = (double)(time_of_flight_sec > 0.0);
effect.horizontal_inches = h_ft * INCHES_PER_FOOT * t_positive;
```

## Physics Implementation (GUNDOM)

### Coriolis Effect with Azimuth Projection

GUNDOM implements the complete Coriolis formula with azimuth projection:

| Component | Formula | Purpose |
|-----------|---------|---------|
| Horizontal | `omega * range * sin(lat) * tof * cos(az)` | Shooter's windage axis |
| Vertical (Eotvos) | `omega * range * cos(lat) * sin(az) * tof` | Critical for Hawaii/Guam users |

### Assert Usage

Development builds include assertions for validation:

```c
ARENA_ASSERT(arena != NULL, "arena is NULL");
ARENA_ASSERT(is_power_of_two(alignment), "alignment not power of 2");
```

## Future Enhancements

1. **Spin Drift**: Γ£à Implemented (Litz formula)
2. **Coriolis Effect**: Γ£à Implemented (with Eotvos)
3. **Custom Drag Curves**: Γ£à Implemented (drag_table.c)
4. **Multi-projectile**: Support for shotgun patterns
5. **Real-time Weather**: Integration with weather APIs","numCharactersInRequestedRange":12049,"totalLinesInFile":352}

## Phase 1: Project Structure Mapping

### 1.1 C Core Modules (11 files in `core/c/`)

| drag_models | drag_models.c | drag_models.h | G1/G7/etc. drag coefficients | drag_table |

### 1.2 Xcode Build Membership

**Currently compiled** (in `PBXSourcesBuildPhase`):
- runtime.c, database.c, ballistics.c, atmosphere.c, drag_models.c, units.c, ops_a64.s

- `arena.c` - Required by `ballistics.c` (if arena allocation is used)
- `bc_curve.c` - May be required by ballistics pipeline

- `truing.c` - Optional truing functionality

## Phase 3: Formal Verification Artifacts

### 3.1 State Machine: Drag Table Lifecycle

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: drag_table_init
    Initialized --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point
    PointsAdded --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point
    PointsAdded --> Sorted: drag_table_sort
    Sorted --> Valid: count >= 2
    Valid --> Persisted: drag_table_save
    Persisted --> Valid: drag_table_load
    Valid --> Interpolating: drag_table_interpolate
    Interpolating --> Valid: return Cd
    Valid --> [*]: drag_table_delete
```

### 3.2 State Machine: Ballistics Calculation Pipeline

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> InputValidation
    InputValidation --> AtmosphereCalc: input valid
    InputValidation --> Error: invalid input
    AtmosphereCalc --> DragModelSelect
    DragModelSelect --> StandardDrag: custom_drag_table == NULL
    DragModelSelect --> CustomDrag: custom_drag_table != NULL
    StandardDrag --> TrajectoryIntegration
    CustomDrag --> TableValidation
    TableValidation --> TrajectoryIntegration: drag_table_is_valid
    TableValidation --> FallbackG1: invalid table
    FallbackG1 --> TrajectoryIntegration
    TrajectoryIntegration --> OutputGeneration
    OutputGeneration --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```

### 3.3 Control Flow Graph: `drag_coefficient_custom`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry[Entry: drag_coefficient_custom]
    check_null{table == NULL?}
    check_valid{drag_table_is_valid?}
    call_g1[drag_coefficient_g1]
    call_interp[drag_table_interpolate]
    exit[Return Cd]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| call_g1
    check_null -->|No| check_valid
    check_valid -->|No| call_g1
    check_valid -->|Yes| call_interp
    call_g1 --> exit
    call_interp --> exit
```

## Root Cause Analysis

The 6 failing CI checks (iOS App Build Debug, SQLite Verification jobs) are **NOT caused by SQLite issues**. The actual failure is a **linker error**:

```
Undefined symbols for architecture arm64:
  "_drag_table_interpolate", referenced from:
      _drag_coefficient_custom in drag_models.o
  "_drag_table_is_valid", referenced from:
      _drag_coefficient_custom in drag_models.o
ld: symbol(s) not found for architecture arm64
```

## Problem

The Xcode project (`ios/App/App.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`) is missing `drag_table.c` from its build sources.

**Files in `core/c/` directory:**
- arena.c, atmosphere.c, ballistics.c, ballistics_cache.c, bc_curve.c, database.c, drag_models.c, **drag_table.c**, runtime.c, truing.c, units.c

**Files currently in Xcode project Sources:**
- atmosphere.c, ballistics.c, database.c, drag_models.c, runtime.c, units.c

**Missing from Xcode project (critical):**
- `drag_table.c` - contains `drag_table_interpolate()` and `drag_table_is_valid()` functions that `drag_models.c` depends on

## Solution

Add `drag_table.c` and `drag_table.h` to the Xcode project configuration in `ios/App/App.xcodeproj/project.pbxproj`:

1. Add PBXFileReference entries for `drag_table.c` and `drag_table.h`
2. Add PBXBuildFile entry for `drag_table.c` in Sources
3. Add files to the C Files group
4. Add the build file to PBXSourcesBuildPhase

## Implementation

This fix should be committed to the `claude/fix-sqlite3-compilation-848Cu` branch in the `ludoplex/BallisticsCalculator-iOS` repository, then pushed to update PR #26.

## Additional Considerations

# BallisticsCalculator-iOS Project Mapping and Verification Artifacts

## Phase 1: Project Structure Mapping

### 1.1 C Core Modules (11 files in `core/c/`)

| Module | Source | Header | Purpose | Dependencies |

|--------|--------|--------|---------|--------------|

| arena | arena.c | arena.h | Memory arena allocator | stdlib |

| atmosphere | atmosphere.c | atmosphere.h | Atmospheric calculations | math |

| ballistics | ballistics.c | ballistics.h | Main trajectory engine | drag_models, atmosphere, drag_table |

| ballistics_cache | ballistics_cache.c | ballistics_cache.h | Computation caching | ballistics |

| bc_curve | bc_curve.c | bc_curve.h | BC curve calculations | math |

| database | database.c | database.h | SQLite persistence | sqlite3 |

| drag_models | drag_models.c | drag_models.h | G1/G7/etc. drag coefficients | drag_table |

| drag_table | drag_table.c | drag_table.h | Custom drag tables | sqlite3 |

| runtime | runtime.c | runtime.h | Runtime utilities | stdlib |

| truing | truing.c | truing.h | Truing calculations | ballistics |

| units | units.c | units.h | Unit conversions | math |

### 1.2 Xcode Build Membership

**Currently compiled** (in `PBXSourcesBuildPhase`):

- runtime.c, database.c, ballistics.c, atmosphere.c, drag_models.c, units.c, ops_a64.s

**Missing from build** (causing linker errors):

- `drag_table.c` - Required by `drag_models.c` (functions: `drag_table_interpolate`, `drag_table_is_valid`)
- `arena.c` - Required by `ballistics.c` (if arena allocation is used)
- `bc_curve.c` - May be required by ballistics pipeline
- `ballistics_cache.c` - Optional caching layer
- `truing.c` - Optional truing functionality

### 1.3 iOS Application Layer

```javascript
ios/App/App/
  AppDelegate.m, main.m, ViewController.m         (Objective-C entry)
  BallisticsApp.swift                             (SwiftUI app)
  Ballistics-Bridging-Header.h                    (C-to-Swift bridge)
  Engine/BallisticsViewModel.swift                (UI-to-C bridge)
  Views/{MainDashboard,ReticleView,RangeCardView,SettingsView}.swift
  Theme/TacticalTheme.swift
```

---

## Phase 2: Dependency Analysis

### 2.1 Include Graph (C Headers)

```mermaid
graph TD
    subgraph external [External Dependencies]
        sqlite3[sqlite3.h]
        stdlib[stdlib.h]
        math[math.h]
    end
    
    subgraph core [Core Modules]
        ballistics_h[ballistics.h]
        drag_models_h[drag_models.h]
        drag_table_h[drag_table.h]
        atmosphere_h[atmosphere.h]
        database_h[database.h]
        arena_h[arena.h]
        units_h[units.h]
        runtime_h[runtime.h]
    end
    
    ballistics_h --> drag_models_h
    ballistics_h --> atmosphere_h
    drag_models_h --> drag_table_h
    drag_table_h --> sqlite3
    database_h --> sqlite3
```



### 2.2 Function Call Graph (Critical Path)

```mermaid
graph LR
    subgraph swift [Swift Layer]
        BallisticsViewModel
    end
    
    subgraph c_api [C API Layer]
        ballistics_solve
        ballistics_trajectory
    end
    
    subgraph physics [Physics Layer]
        drag_coefficient
        drag_coefficient_custom
        drag_table_interpolate
        drag_table_is_valid
        atmosphere_density
    end
    
    BallisticsViewModel --> ballistics_solve
    ballistics_solve --> drag_coefficient
    drag_coefficient --> drag_coefficient_custom
    drag_coefficient_custom --> drag_table_is_valid
    drag_coefficient_custom --> drag_table_interpolate
    ballistics_solve --> atmosphere_density
```

---

## Phase 3: Formal Verification Artifacts

### 3.1 State Machine: Drag Table Lifecycle

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> Uninitialized
    Uninitialized --> Initialized: drag_table_init
    Initialized --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point
    PointsAdded --> PointsAdded: drag_table_add_point
    PointsAdded --> Sorted: drag_table_sort
    Sorted --> Valid: count >= 2
    Valid --> Persisted: drag_table_save
    Persisted --> Valid: drag_table_load
    Valid --> Interpolating: drag_table_interpolate
    Interpolating --> Valid: return Cd
    Valid --> [*]: drag_table_delete
```



### 3.2 State Machine: Ballistics Calculation Pipeline

```mermaid
stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> InputValidation
    InputValidation --> AtmosphereCalc: input valid
    InputValidation --> Error: invalid input
    AtmosphereCalc --> DragModelSelect
    DragModelSelect --> StandardDrag: custom_drag_table == NULL
    DragModelSelect --> CustomDrag: custom_drag_table != NULL
    StandardDrag --> TrajectoryIntegration
    CustomDrag --> TableValidation
    TableValidation --> TrajectoryIntegration: drag_table_is_valid
    TableValidation --> FallbackG1: invalid table
    FallbackG1 --> TrajectoryIntegration
    TrajectoryIntegration --> OutputGeneration
    OutputGeneration --> [*]
    Error --> [*]
```



### 3.3 Control Flow Graph: `drag_coefficient_custom`

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    entry[Entry: drag_coefficient_custom]
    check_null{table == NULL?}
    check_valid{drag_table_is_valid?}
    call_g1[drag_coefficient_g1]
    call_interp[drag_table_interpolate]
    exit[Return Cd]
    
    entry --> check_null
    check_null -->|Yes| call_g1
    check_null -->|No| check_valid
    check_valid -->|No| call_g1
    check_valid -->|Yes| call_interp
    call_g1 --> exit
    call_interp --> exit
```



### 3.4 Low-Level Symbol Table (Expected in Binary)

For programmatic verification, the compiled binary must export these symbols:| Symbol | Object File | Required By |

|--------|-------------|-------------|

| `_ballistics_init` | ballistics.o | runtime |

| `_ballistics_solve` | ballistics.o | BallisticsViewModel |

| `_ballistics_trajectory` | ballistics.o | RangeCardView |

| `_drag_coefficient` | drag_models.o | ballistics.o |

| `_drag_coefficient_custom` | drag_models.o | ballistics.o |

| `_drag_table_interpolate` | **drag_table.o** | drag_models.o |

| `_drag_table_is_valid` | **drag_table.o** | drag_models.o |

| `_drag_table_init` | **drag_table.o** | database.o |

| `_atmosphere_density` | atmosphere.o | ballistics.o |---

## Phase 4: Verification Scripts

### 4.1 Symbol Verification (nm/objdump)

Create script to verify all required symbols are present in the compiled binary:

```powershell
# verify-symbols.ps1
$required_symbols = @(
    "_drag_table_interpolate",
    "_drag_table_is_valid",
    "_drag_coefficient_custom",
    "_ballistics_solve"
)
# Run nm on binary, check each symbol exists
```



### 4.2 Include Dependency Verification

Create script to parse C files and verify all `#include` dependencies are satisfied:

```powershell
# verify-includes.ps1
# Parse all .c files, extract #include statements
# Verify corresponding .h files exist and are in HEADER_SEARCH_PATHS
```



### 4.3 Xcode Project Consistency Check

Create script to verify `project.pbxproj` contains all required source files:

```powershell
# verify-pbxproj.ps1
# Parse project.pbxproj
# Verify each .c file in core/c/ has:
#   - PBXFileReference entry
#   - PBXBuildFile entry
#   - Entry in PBXSourcesBuildPhase
```

3. **Control flow graphs** (Mermaid) for critical functions
4. **Symbol verification script** (PowerShell) for binary validation
5. **Include verification script** (PowerShell) for build consistency
